            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_MA1">MA</gloss>
                    Palestine/4–649</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-06">April 6,
                    1949</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: In accordance with Section 1 of
                    the Joint Resolution providing for the authorization of a special contribution
                    by the United States for the relief of Palestine refugees (Public Law 25, 81st
                    Congress, approved March 24, 1949), I have today allocated $8,000,000 to the
                    Department of State from funds advanced by the Reconstruction Finance
                    Corporation under the provisions of Section 2 of the aforementioned Act, which
                    advance has been deposited with the Treasury of the United States, and
                    established under Appropriation Symbol No. 119/00043.</p>
                <p>These funds are to be used by the Department of State as a special contribution
                    to the United Nations for the purposes set forth in the resolution of the
                    General Assembly of the United Nations of November 19, 1948, providing for the
                    relief of Palestine refugees.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
